                     </persName>
                     
                   had lately served our Lord the King, as a seaman on board the Carysfort, and that certain prize-money was due to him for such service, on the <rs id="t17850511-12-cd65" type="crimeDate">18th of April</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17850511-12-off64 t17850511-12-cd65"></join> last, feloniously did forge and counterfeit a certain letter of attorney to him the said 
                     <persName id="t17850511-12-person187">
                        Robert
                         Jackson
                     <interp inst="t17850511-12-person187" type="surname" value="Jackson"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17850511-12-person187" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17850511-12-person187" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , purporting to be signed, sealed, and delivered by him, the said 
                     <persName id="t17850511-12-person188">
                        Benjamin
                         Bell
                     <interp inst="t17850511-12-person188" type="surname" value="Bell"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17850511-12-person188" type="given" value="Benjamin"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17850511-12-person188" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , in order to receive certain prize-money, then supposed to be due to him the said Benjamin, for, and on account of his service supposed to have been done on board the said ship
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>A second count, For uttering the same, with intent to defraud 
               
                  <persName id="t17850511-12-victim190" type="victimName">
                     Isaac 
                     Clementson
                  <interp inst="t17850511-12-victim190" type="surname" value="Clementson"></interp>
